<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="69" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[140,1108,448,791]" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[140,267,448,474]" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis box="[140,262,448,474]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="69" reason="1">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The new species is very similar to the Costa Rican 
<taxonomicName authority="Gauld" authorityName="Gauld" authorityYear="2000" box="[834,1080,448,474]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Labena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guanacasteca">
<emphasis box="[834,1003,449,474]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">L. guanacasteca</emphasis>
Gauld
</taxonomicName>
as both have a fore wing without an apical black spot, a propodeum with area superomedia open posteriorly and broadly confluent with area petiolaris (
<figureCitation box="[852,919,518,545]" captionStart="Figs 5-6" captionStartId="6.[140,184,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[165,1080,1169,1592]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[164,1083,1163,1602]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 5-6. Labena spp., areolation of propodeum, dorsoposterior view: 5 – L. acerba sp. n., ♀ (holotype); 6 – L. tarsata Gauld, ♀, var. (Cañón del Novillo, 27.IV.1985)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3786960" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3786960/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), and a first sternite with distinct transverse ridge centrally (Fig. 4). Unlike this species 
<taxonomicName authority="Khalaim &amp; Ruiz-Cancino, 2009" authorityName="Khalaim &amp; Ruiz-Cancino" authorityYear="2009" box="[939,1039,554,580]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Labena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acerba" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[939,1039,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">L. acerba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1046,1107,554,580]" pageId="4" pageNumber="69" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has a black flagellum, without a pale median band (Fig. 3), a shorter area superomedia + petiolaris of propodeum (
<figureCitation box="[456,524,624,651]" captionStart="Figs 5-6" captionStartId="6.[140,184,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[165,1080,1169,1592]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[164,1083,1163,1602]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 5-6. Labena spp., areolation of propodeum, dorsoposterior view: 5 – L. acerba sp. n., ♀ (holotype); 6 – L. tarsata Gauld, ♀, var. (Cañón del Novillo, 27.IV.1985)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3786960" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3786960/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), and a yellow body without any black marks. The new species can be distinguished from all Mexican species of 
<taxonomicName box="[834,915,659,685]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Labena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[834,915,659,685]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">Labena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following characters in combination: 1) mesopleuron polished, impunctate, 2) fore wing without an apical spot, 3) first sternite with a transverse ridge, 4) flagellum extensively black, without a central yellowish band.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3786958" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3786958" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3786958/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="69" startId="4.[140,184,1622,1644]" targetBox="[140,1108,844,1602]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[140,1108,1622,1676]" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[140,231,1622,1644]" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">Figs |-4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Khalaim &amp; Ruiz-Cancino, 2009" authorityName="Khalaim &amp; Ruiz-Cancino" authorityYear="2009" box="[237,365,1622,1643]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Labena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acerba" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[237,365,1622,1643]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">Labena acerba</emphasis>
